The '''1986–87''' season was the 85th in the history of the [[Western Football League]].

The league champions for the second time in their history were [[Saltash United F.C.|Saltash United]]. The champions of Division One were [[Swanage Town & Herston F.C.|Swanage Town & Herston]].<ref name="Robinson">Robinson, Michael (ed.), Non-League Football Tables 1889–2006, Soccer Books, 2006</ref>

==Final tables==

===Premier Division===
The Premier Division remained at 22 clubs after [[Shepton Mallet F.C.|Shepton Mallet Town]] were relegated and left to join the [[Somerset County League]]. One club joined:

*[[Radstock Town F.C.|Radstock Town]], runners-up in the First Division.
